main event: An unidentified object resembling a round plate was observed over Finland on 12 February 1961.
interesting points: The object exhibited some fluctuation of light during the observation.,It was described as having edges that were not sharply defined.,The sighting lasted for a total of 10 minutes.,The object disappeared from sight while in the middle of its path of travel.,Conclusions suggest the object may have been an astronomical phenomenon but could not be definitively evaluated.
witness description: Pilots from four Finnish planes flying above cloud formation.
